60: { introduction: "Welcome to Financial Fresh Start: Recovery Edition. Facing the financial damage of addiction takes enormous courage. This course holds your hand through every step — from the first terrifying look at the numbers to building a real plan forward.", detailedOutcomes: ["Complete a full, honest financial assessment without judgment", "Create a realistic recovery budget that accounts for treatment costs", "Prioritize debts strategically using the avalanche or snowball method", "Begin building an emergency fund, even if it starts with $5", "Communicate with creditors about your situation and negotiate terms", "Practice financial self-forgiveness alongside practical repair", "Set up a simple tracking system for income and expenses", "Develop a 6-month financial recovery roadmap"] },
61: { introduction: "Welcome to Budgeting & Money Management. A budget isn't a cage — it's a map. It shows you where your money is going and lets you decide where you want it to go instead.", detailedOutcomes: ["Choose and implement a budgeting method that fits your personality", "Track every dollar for at least 30 consecutive days", "Reduce unnecessary expenses by at least 15% without feeling deprived", "Build an automated savings habit, no matter how small", "Use digital budgeting tools effectively", "Conduct a monthly financial review and adjustment", "Plan for irregular expenses that derail most budgets", "Build confidence in your ability to manage money"] },
