66: { introduction: "Welcome to Entrepreneurship in Recovery. Recovery teaches you everything an entrepreneur needs: resilience, adaptability, comfort with discomfort, and the ability to start over. This course channels that energy into building something of your own.", detailedOutcomes: ["Identify viable business ideas that leverage your unique experience and skills", "Create a lean business plan focused on minimum viable product", "Understand startup funding options appropriate for your situation", "Build basic marketing skills for a small business", "Manage entrepreneurial stress without compromising recovery", "Separate business finances from personal finances from day one", "Know when to seek mentorship and where to find it", "Build a business that supports rather than threatens your recovery"] },

