74: { introduction: "Welcome to Family Recovery: Healing Together. Addiction is a family disease — it changes the dynamics, roles, and emotional landscape for everyone in the household. Healing means the whole family transforms.", detailedOutcomes: ["Understand addiction's impact on family systems and dynamics", "Identify and break dysfunctional family roles (hero, scapegoat, mascot, lost child)", "Improve family communication using structured techniques", "Set loving boundaries that support everyone's recovery", "Distinguish between supporting and enabling family members", "Know when and how to engage family therapy", "Create a healthier family culture with new patterns and traditions", "Support each family member's individual healing process"] },
