81: { introduction: "Welcome to Relapse Prevention Fundamentals. Relapse is not a sudden event — it's a process that begins long before you pick up a substance. Understanding this process is your best defense against it.", detailedOutcomes: ["Identify all three stages of relapse: emotional, mental, and physical", "Recognize your personal early warning signs before they escalate", "Build a comprehensive, written relapse prevention plan", "Create an emergency action plan for crisis moments", "Understand relapse risk factors and how to mitigate each one", "Implement daily practices that maintain your recovery foundation", "Communicate your prevention plan to your support network", "Update your prevention plan regularly as your recovery evolves"] },
